16:["$","h2",null,{"children":"The Technology Paradox in Crane Operations"}]
17:["$","p",null,{"children":"A modern all-terrain crane can cost $2-10 million. It has GPS tracking, load moment indicators, anti-two-block systems, wind speed sensors, and cellular telematics that report engine diagnostics to the manufacturer in real time."}]
18:["$","p",null,{"children":"And the daily inspection for that $10 million machine? A clipboard. A carbon-copy form. Maybe a spreadsheet if the company is \"advanced.\""}]
19:["$","p",null,{"children":"This paradox exists because crane OEMs sell machines, not compliance workflows. They'll tell you when an engine filter needs changing. They won't tell you when your annual comprehensive inspection is overdue, whether your competent person designation is documented, or whether your wire rope inspection records meet OSHA 1926.1413 requirements."}]
1a:["$","h2",null,{"children":"What's Driving the Digital Shift"}]
1b:["$","h3",null,{"children":"1. OSHA Enforcement Is Getting Sharper"}]
1c:["$","p",null,{"children":"OSHA's National Emphasis Program on crane safety continues to drive targeted inspections on construction sites. Compliance officers are increasingly asking for digital records — not because they're required to be digital, but because organized digital records demonstrate a systematic safety program. Paper binders with missing pages do the opposite."}]
1d:["$","h3",null,{"children":"2. Insurance Carriers Are Demanding Documentation"}]
1e:["$","p",null,{"children":"Crane insurance premiums have risen 15-30% over the past three years. Carriers are responding by demanding more comprehensive documentation of inspection and maintenance programs as a condition of coverage. Companies with digital inspection trails and complete histories are getting better rates — and companies without them are getting non-renewed."}]
1f:["$","h3",null,{"children":"3. General Contractors Are Requiring It"}]
20:["$","p",null,{"children":"Large GCs — the companies that control the biggest, most profitable jobsites — are increasingly requiring subcontractors to demonstrate digital safety management systems during prequalification. If your inspection records are in paper binders, you're losing bids to competitors who can provide digital audit trails."}]
21:["$","h3",null,{"children":"4. The Workforce Is Changing"}]
22:["$","p",null,{"children":"The crane operators and safety directors entering the workforce in 2026 grew up with smartphones. They expect digital tools. Asking them to fill out carbon-copy forms feels like asking them to use a fax machine. Retention and recruitment improve when you give your team modern tools."}]
23:["$","h2",null,{"children":"What Digital Crane Inspection Actually Looks Like"}]
24:["$","p",null,{"children":"Moving from paper to digital isn't just about replacing binders with PDFs. A proper digital crane inspection system should transform the entire compliance workflow:"}]
25:["$","h3",null,{"children":"Pre-Shift Inspections"}]
26:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"Operator completes inspection on their phone or tablet in the cab"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"GPS-tagged, timestamped, tied to the specific crane and operator"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Deficiency photos attached inline — not described in words, shown in pictures"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Automatic alerts to the safety director if critical deficiencies are flagged"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Complete audit trail: who inspected, when, where, and what they found"}]]}]
27:["$","h3",null,{"children":"Periodic and Annual Inspections"}]
28:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"Inspection templates aligned to OSHA 1926.1412 and ANSI B30 requirements"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Inspector qualifications linked to the inspection record"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Automatic tracking of next-due dates across the entire fleet"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Escalating alerts before deadlines — 90, 60, 30, 7 days"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Corrective action tracking from finding through resolution"}]]}]
29:["$","h3",null,{"children":"Fleet-Wide Visibility"}]
2a:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"Dashboard showing every crane's inspection status at a glance"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Traffic light system: green (current), yellow (approaching due date), red (overdue)"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Sortable by location, crane type, inspector, or date range"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"One-click audit report generation for any crane or time period"}]]}]
2b:["$","h2",null,{"children":"The ConExpo Takeaway"}]
2c:["$","p",null,{"children":"ConExpo 2026 proves that the crane industry is embracing technology at the hardware level. The machines are getting smarter every cycle. The question for crane companies isn't whether to go digital — it's how fast."}]
2d:["$","p",null,{"children":"The companies that digitize their inspection and compliance workflows now will have years of organized data, established audit trails, and proven systems by the time their competitors start looking for solutions. In a world where OSHA enforcement is increasing, insurance carriers are demanding documentation, and GCs are requiring digital safety management — early adoption isn't just smart. It's a competitive advantage that compounds over time."}]
2e:["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-navy py-16 px-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4","children":"Go Digital Before Your Competitors Do"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto","children":"CraneCheck is the modern crane inspection platform built for companies ready to leave paper behind. Mobile inspections, automatic scheduling, and audit-ready reports."}],["$","$Lf",null,{"href":"/pricing","className":"bg-brand hover:bg-brand-dark text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold transition-colors","children":"Start Free Trial →"}]]}]}]
